Question 1
flintstones = ["Fred", "Barney", "Wilma", "Betty", "BamBam", "Pebbles"]

flintstones = %w(Fred Barney Wilma Betty BamBam Pebbles)

Question 2
flintstones.push("Dino")
or
flintstones << "Dino"

Question 3
flintstones.push("Dino").push("Hoppy")
or
flintstones.concat(%w(Dino Hoppy))

Question 4
advice.slice!(0, advice.index('house'))

if you used slice, it would return the first part of the sentence but
 the variable would remain unchanged.

Question 5
statement.scan('t').count

scan goes through the string and matches the perimeter given to 
determine if that perimeter is within the string
if so, count will count how many times it is. 

